                        <div class="xr_txt Normal_text xr_s1" style="position: absolute; left:107px; top:1421px; width:853px; height:10px;">
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: -11.77px;">If you take a close look at the grout in the gaps separating tiles of virtually any type, you will notice that it is not actually smooth. No matter how </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 2.75px;">smooth it appears, it is porous, and therefore highly permeable. When a pollutant laden liquid remains in contact with something as porous as grout, </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 17.27px;">the pollutants seep into those pores, and do not come out. You not only want your tile, and grout to look as good as possible, but you also want them </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 31.8px;">to be clean beyond what the naked eye can detect. In addition to not looking as good as it could, a tile, or grout problem can lead to a myriad of </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 46.32px;">other problems, and potentially even health issues.</span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 75.36px;">A genuine issue in any part of your home can be mold. Mold comes in a myriad of forms, and are common in a wide variety of places in your home. </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 89.88px;">Although most molds are harmless, or only an annoyance, some types can be hazardous to your health, and some can even lead to death. Routine </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 104.4px;">tile, and grout cleaning by a Hampton Tile and Grout experts can help your household remain free of mold, and mildew related problems.</span>
