                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: -11.77px;">If you take a close look at the grout in the gaps separating tiles </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 2.75px;">of virtually any type, you will notice that it is not actually smooth. </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 17.27px;">No matter how smooth it appears, it is porous and therefore </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 31.8px;">highly permeable. When a pollutant laden liquid remains in </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 46.32px;">contact with something as porous as grout, the pollutants seep </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 60.84px;">into those pores, and do not come out. You not only want your </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 75.36px;">tile to look as good as possible, but you also what the to be </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 89.88px;">clean beyond what the naked eye can detect. In addition to not </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 104.4px;">looking as good as it could, a tile job can lead to a myriad of </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 118.92px;">other issues, and potentially even health issues.</span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 147.97px;">A genuine issue in any part of your home can be mold. Mold </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 162.49px;">comes in a myriad of forms, and are common in a wide variety </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 177.01px;">of places in your home. Although most molds are harmless, or </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 191.53px;">only an annoyance, some types can be hazardous to your </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 206.05px;">health, and some can even lead to death. Routine tile, and grout </span>
                            <span class="xr_tl Normal_text xr_s1" style="top: 220.57px;">cleaning by a Hampton Tile and Grout experts can help your </span>
